TRUSTABLE-SOFTWARE: This
release of JSON-Library
also referred in the
documentation as nlohmann/json
library is Trustable.

TT-EXPECTATIONS: Documentation
is provided within eclipse-score/inc_nlohmann_json,
specifying what the nlohmann/json
library is expected to
do, and what it must
not do, and how this
is verified.

PJD-03: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library parses all texts
that conform to the JSON
grammar.

NPF-02: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library parses numbers
according to RFC8259.

NPF-02.1: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses integers
without exponent within
the precision of int64_t.

NPF-02.10: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library ignores trailing
zeroes after the decimal
point.

NPF-02.11: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses numbers
within the 64-bit double
range but outside of
the double precision
without throwing an exception
and without guarantee
of precision.

NPF-02.12: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library ignores capitalisation
of the exponent.

NPF-02.2: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses integers
with exponent within
the precision of 64-bit
double.

NPF-02.3: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses floating
point values without
exponent within the precision
of 64-bit double.

NPF-02.4: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses floating
point values with exponent
within the precision
of 64-bit double.

NPF-02.5: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library ignores leading
zeroes in the exponent.

NPF-02.6: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses integers
within IEEE 754-2008
binary64.

NPF-02.7: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library ignores leading
and trailing whitespace.

NPF-02.8: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library ignores one singular
leading plus of the exponent.

NPF-02.9: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library parses floating
point numbers within
IEEE 754-2008 binary64
standard.

TA-BEHAVIOURS: Expected
or required behaviours
for the nlohmann/json
library are identified,
specified, verified and
validated based on analysis.
